

Set up

1. Install git on your local and check if it correctly installed

    git --version
    git -v

2. Create a GitHub account anf set global information for git

git config  --global user.name ada.arbab1


3. Check your Github/GitLab/Bitbucket and make sure the default branch is matching the one you set for local
Setting /Repositories/Default Branch

4. Set up am SSH keys whoich is used instead of password while you push or pull code
pushing code = sending your code from local repository to remote repository
pulling code = achieving 